org.jpws.pwslib.order
Class DefaultRecordWrapper

java.lang.Object
  org.jpws.pwslib.order.DefaultRecordWrapper
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable, Collatable
public class DefaultRecordWrapper
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable, Collatable, java.lang.Cloneable

This class wraps a PwsRecord for purposes of quick reference to a listing sort value derived from and belonging to the record.

Mutability Status: This class walks from the assumption that the record fields constituting the sort value (namely GROUP and TITLE) will not likely change during the lifetime (validity) of an instance. Hence the sort value is not recalculated except through the use of refresh(). The general practice is to substitute wrappers of a record by a new instance whenever a permanent modification occurs on the referenced record's content.

Since:
0-3-0
